Murdoch Tells Investors News Corp. Must Be ‘Principled’ Company

-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 
2011-10-21T17:20:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/murdoch-tells-investors-news-corp-must-be-principled-company.html
Rupert Murdoch , addressing  News
Corp. (NWSA) ’s phone-hacking scandal, told shareholders at the annual
meeting today the company must be principled.  “We cannot just be a profitable company,” Murdoch, the
company’s chairman and chief executive, said at the meeting in
 Los Angeles . “We must be a princpled company. I am personally
committed to right any wrong that was committed.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
